    {q:'Under the equity method, dividends received from an investee are:',o:['Investment income on the income statement','A reduction of the investment account','An increase in the investment account','Revenue from operations'],a:1,e:'Dividends reduce the carrying value of the investment — they are a partial return of capital, not income under the equity method.'},
    {q:'A deferred tax liability arises when:',o:['Accounting income exceeds taxable income','Taxable income exceeds accounting income','Revenue is recognised for tax before accounting','Depreciation methods are the same'],a:0,e:'DTL arises when accounting income > taxable income. Taxes are higher in future periods — e.g. accelerated tax depreciation lowers taxable income now, raises it later.'},
    {q:'Under IFRS, pension remeasurements are reported in:',o:['Income statement as pension cost','Other Comprehensive Income','Retained earnings directly','Footnotes only'],a:1,e:'IFRS requires actuarial gains/losses and the difference between actual and expected return on plan assets to go to OCI, never reclassified to P&L.'},
    {q:'Ownership above 50% of a subsidiary requires:',o:['Equity method','Proportionate consolidation','Full consolidation with non-controlling interest','Fair value method'],a:2,e:'Control (>50%) requires full consolidation under both IFRS and US GAAP. 100% of subsidiary assets/liabilities consolidated; NCI shown separately in equity.'},
    {q:'Funded status of a defined benefit pension equals:',o:['ABO minus plan assets','Fair value of plan assets minus PBO','Service cost minus contributions','Past service cost plus interest cost'],a:1,e:'Funded Status = Fair Value of Plan Assets − PBO. Positive = overfunded (asset); Negative = underfunded (liability on balance sheet).'}
   ]},
  {id:'cor',name:'Corporate Finance',ico:'◬',col:'#854F0B',bg:'#FAEEDA',sub:'Capital budgeting, WACC & dividends',
